ople]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Brisbane]]\n[[Category:Australian soccer players]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:England youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football goalkeepers]]\n[[Category:Reading F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Rushden & Diamonds F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Wycombe Wanderers F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Aldershot Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Basingstoke Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Whitehawk F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Hayes & Yeading United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Brisbane Roar FC players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:National League (English football) players]]\n[[Category:A-League players]]\n[[Category:Australian expatriate soccer players]]\n[[Category:People educated at Padua College (Brisbane)]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in England]]\n[[Category:English people of Scottish descent]]\n[[Category:English people of Sri Lankan descent]]\n[[Category:Australian people of Scottish descent]]\n[[Category:Australian people of Sri Lankan descent]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the assistant coach|Jamie Young (basketball)}}\n{{EngvarB|date=July 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Jamie Young\n| image = Jamie Young.JPG\n| caption = Young playing for [[Aldershot Town F.C.|Aldershot Town]] in 2010\n| image_size = 200\n| fullname = Jamie Iain Young\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1985|8|25|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Brisbane]], Australia\n| height = {{height|ft=5|in=11}}<ref>{{cite web|title=Jamie Young|url=http://www.brisbaneroar.com.au/player/jamie-young/1xwl0pga3saze1pl3f1a8tqz6v|publisher=Brisbane Roar FC|accessdate=6 February 2017}}</ref>\n| position = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| currentclub = [[Brisbane Roar FC|Brisbane Roar]]\n| clubnumber = 21\n| youthyears1 = 2002\u20132003\n| youthclubs1 = [[Reading F.C.|Reading]]\n| years1 = 2003\u20132006\n| years2 = 2005\u20132006\n| years3 = 2006\u20132010\n| years4 = 2010\u20132013\n| years5 = 2013\n| years6 = 2013\n| years7 = 2013\u20132014\n| years8 = 2014\u2013\n| clubs1 = [[Reading F.C.|Reading]]\n| clubs2 = \u2192 [[Rushden & Diamonds F.C.|Rushden & Diamonds]] (loan)\n| clubs3 = [[Wycombe Wanderers F.C.|Wycombe Wanderers]]\n| clubs4 = [[Aldershot Town F.C.|Aldershot Town]]\n| clubs5 = [[Basingstoke Town F.C.|Basingstoke Town]]\n| clubs6 = [[Whitehawk F.C.|Whitehawk]]\n| clubs7 = [[Hayes & Yeading United F.C.|Hayes & Yeading United]]\n| clubs8 = [[Brisbane Roar FC|Brisbane Roar]]\n| caps1 = 1\n| goals1 = 0\n| caps2 = 20\n| goals2 = 0\n| caps3 = 39\n| goals3 = 0\n| caps4 = 124\n| goals4 = 0\n| caps5 = 1\n| goals5 = 0\n| caps6 = 1\n| goals6 = 0\n| caps7 = 10\n| goals7 = 0\n| caps8 = 98\n| goals8 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 2002\u20132003\n| nationalteam1 = [[England national under-18 football team|England U18]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 3\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2003\n| nationalteam2 = [[England national under-19 football team|England U19]]\n| nationalcaps2 = 1\n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| nationalyears3 = 2005\n| nationalteam3 = [[England national under-20 football team|England U20]]\n| nationalcaps3 = 4\n| nationalgoals3 = 0\n| club-update = 26 April 2019\n}}\n\n'''Jamie Iain Young''' (born 25 August 1985) is [[Goalkeeper (association football)|football goalkeeper]] who plays for [[A-League]] side [[Brisbane Roar FC|Brisbane Roar]]. Born in Australia, Young was a youth international for England.\n\n==Personal life==\nBorn in [[Brisbane]], Australia, Young is of Sri Lankan and Scottish descent.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://shop.theshots.co.uk/PlayerDisplay.ink?skip=32&squadno=43268&season=12/13&seasonl=2012/2013&Playertype=P |title=Jamie Young |publisher=Aldershot Town F.C |accessdate=23 October 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160729170929/http://shop.theshots.co.uk/PlayerDisplay.ink?skip=32&season=12%2F13&squadno=43268&seasonl=2012%2F2013&Playertype=P |archive-date=29 July 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\nYoung is currently studying Bachelor of Health degree, which he placed on hold in July 2016 in order to focus on his football, having previously combined university studies with football commitments for more than six years.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Monteverde|first1=Marco|title=Brisbane Roar goalkeeper Jamie Young suspends studies as he seeks to nail down No.1 spot|url=http://www.couriermail.com.au/sport/football/a-league/brisbane-roar-goalkeeper-jamie-young-suspends-studies-as-he-seeks-to-nail-down-no1-spot/news-story/dc7256ef2a86c1f1510f24a1810518ca|accessdate=28 February 2017|work=The Courier Mail|date=26 August 2016}}</ref>\n\nYoung is an ambassador for the Multicultural Development Association, which helps refugees and migrants settle in Queensland.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Monteverde|first1=Marco|title=Brisbane Roar goalkeeper Jamie Young suspends studies as he seeks to nail down No.1 spot|url=http://www.couriermail.com.au/sport/football/a-league/brisbane-roar-goalkeeper-jamie-young-suspends-studies-as-he-seeks-to-nail-down-no1-spot/news-story/dc7256ef2a86c1f1510f24a1810518ca|accessdate=28 February 2017|work=The Courier Mail|date=26 August 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\nHaving grown up in Australia, he attended [[Padua College, Brisbane|Padua College]], where he played in the First XI as Goalkeeper and also played at Pine Hills, Albany Creek, Easts and QAS at club level. Young moved to England in 2002 to play professional football for [[Reading F.C.|Reading]]. After failing to break into the first team, he was released by [[Reading F.C.|Reading]] on 8 May 2006, and subsequently signed a one-year deal with [[Wycombe Wanderers F.C.|Wycombe Wanderers]] on 2 August 2006.\n\nHe missed much of the [[2007-08 in English football|2007\u201308 season]] with a knee injury, but regained fitness by the end of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wycombewanderers.premiumtv.co.uk/page/ProfilesDetail/0,,10430~15200,00.html |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080706133740/http://www.wycombewanderers.co.uk/page/ProfilesDetail/0%2C%2C10430~15200%2C00.html |archivedate= 6 July 2008 |title=Jamie Young |publisher=[[Wycombe Wanderers F.C.]] |accessdate=23 October 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref> His contract was cancelled by mutual consent in January 2010 after he was informed that he would not be offered a new contract in the summer. He was signed on a non-contract basis by Aldershot Town of League Two on 11 March 2010 as cover for goalkeeper [[Mikhael Jaimez-Ruiz]].<ref>{{cite web |date=11 March 2010 |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/a/aldershot/8562404.stm |title=Aldershot sign former Reading duo Brown and Young |publisher=BBC Sport |accessdate=11 March 2010}}</ref>\n\nAfter impressing and establishing himself as the first choice goalkeeper, in the last quarter of the [[2009\u201310 Football League Two|2009\u201310 season]], where Aldershot Town qualified for the [[Football League Two|League Two]] [[Football League Two play-offs|play-offs]], Young signed a one-year contract with the club in June 2010. With the arrival of new goalkeeper [[Ross Worner]] in the 2011\u201312 season, Young was demoted to second choice goalkeeper but still managed to make a number of appearances in the later stage of the season when Worner was ruled out with a back injury. On 24 June 2012, Young signed a one-year contract to keep him with Aldershot until 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www1.skysports.com/football/news/12691/7838878/Young-extends-Shots-contract |title=Young extends Shots contract |publisher=Sky Sports |accessdate=23 October 2013}}</ref>\n[[File:Jamie Young Save.jpg|thumb|Jamie Young makes a save from a Melbourne City Free Kick 01.03.20]]\nYoung left Aldershot in June 2013 after the club were relegated from the [[Football League]] and placed in administration.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://au.fourfourtwo.com/news/279161,youngs-fight-for-an-a-league-chance.aspx |last=Stone |first=Kathy |date=13 August 2013 |title=Young's fight for an A-League chance |publisher=Australian FourFourTwo |accessdate=23 October 2013}}</ref> He played one game for [[Basingstoke Town F.C.|Basingstoke Town]] in September as cover for their regular goalkeeper before joining fellow [[Conference South]] side [[Whitehawk F.C.|Whitehawk]] the following month.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.basingstokegazette.co.uk/sport/10690949.Basingstoke_manager_Jason_Bristow_believes_his_side_can_match_any_in_their_league/ |last=Merry |first=Graham |date=23 September 2013 |title=Basingstoke manager Jason Bristow believes his side can match any in their league |newspaper=Basingstoke Gazette |accessdate=23 October 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://nonleague.pitchero.com/news/whitehawk-add-keeper-and-striker-25732/#_ |title=Whitehawk add keeper and striker |publisher=Pitchero Non League |accessdate=23 October 2013}}</ref> After making only one appearance he moved, this time joining [[Hayes & Yeading United F.C.|Hayes & Yeading United]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://nonleague.pitchero.com/news/new-keeper-for-hayes-yeading-26196/ |title=New keeper for Hayes & Yeading |publisher=Pitchero Non League |accessdate=27 October 2013}}</ref> After making 10 appearances for Hayes & Yeading during its 2013\u201314 [[Conference South]] campaign, Young was released by manager [[Phil Babb]] following an on-field altercation with a teammate in a 2\u20130 defeat to [[Bath City F.C.|Bath City]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.getwestlondon.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/hayes--yeading-take-action-6674617 |title=Hayes & Yeading to take action against 'disgraceful' duo |publisher=Get West London |date=5 February 2014 |accessdate=10 May 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.westlondonsport.com/features-comment/phil-babb-colum-hayes-yeading83833 |title=I let Jamie Young go to fund new signings \u2013 and I'd like a striker |publisher=West London Sport |date=7 March 2014 |accessdate=10 May 2014 }}</ref>\n\nOn 10 May 2014, it was reported that Young would return to his hometown to join [[A-League]] defending champion [[Brisbane Roar FC|Brisbane Roar]] for the 2014\u201315 season. Young struggled to adjust to the A-League with fans and even teammate [[Shane Stefanutto]] laying the blame on Young for the Roar's less than impressive start to the season. Young kept his first cleansheet in a 4\u20130 thrashing of the [[Newcastle Jets FC|Newcastle Jets]], courtesy of an [[Henrique Andrade Silva|Henrique]] hat-trick. Due to [[Michael Theo]]'s wrist injury, sustained in pre-season training, Young played as the first choice goalkeeper for the majority of the season, even in the Elimination Final clash against [[Adelaide United FC|Adelaide United]] in which Brisbane lost 2\u20131. Young played 24 matches for the Roar in the 2014&ndash;15 season, keeping five clean-sheets, as well as one clean-sheet in the ACL in Roar's 1\u20130 win against [[Urawa Red Diamonds|Urawa Reds]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.adelaidenow.com.au/sport/football/brisbane-roar-sign-english-goalkeeper-jamie-young/story-fnk6pqha-1226912709685 |title=Brisbane Roar sign English goalkeeper Jamie Young |publisher=The Advertiser |date=10 May 2014 |accessdate=10 May 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.couriermail.com.au/sport/football/brisbane-roar-duo-shane-stefanutto-and-jamie-young-involved-in-heated-argument-after-loss-to-city/story-fnii0fy2-1227117101191 |title=Brisbane Roar duo Shane Stefanutto and Jamie Young involved in heated argument after loss to City\n |publisher=Courier Mail |date=8 November 2014 |accessdate=9 November 2014 }}</ref>\n\nOn 30 April, Young won the golden glove award for best goalkeeper in the A-League at the Dolan Warren Awards.\n\n==International career==\nAlthough born in Australia, Young has elected to play for [[England national football team|England]] internationally, having been capped for the U20 team to date.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefa.com/England/U20s/NewsAndFeatures/Postings/2005/06/Toulon_EnglandvPortugal.htm |archive-url=https://archive.is/20071029051823/http://www.thefa.com/England/U20s/NewsAndFeatures/Postings/2005/06/Toulon_EnglandvPortugal.htm |url-status=dead |archive-date=29 October 2007 |title=Portugal edge Toulon win |publisher=The Football Association |date=4 June 2005 |accessdate=23 October 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|match played 12 December 2014.}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.soccerbase.com/players/player.sd?player_id=33301 |title=Jamie Young |work=Soccerbase |publisher=Centurycomm |accessdate=23 October 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.basingstoketown.net/statistics/?GTTabs=2 |title=Jamie Young's playing record |publisher=Basingstoke Town F.C |accessdate=23 October 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130703104844/http://www.basingstoketown.net/statistics/?GTTabs=2 |archivedate= 3 July 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/jamie-young/50780/ |title=J. Young |publisher=Soccerway |accessdate=23 October 2013}}</ref>\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Club\n!rowspan=2|Season\n!colspan=3|League\n!colspan=2|[[FA Cup]]\n!colspan=2|[[Football League Cup|League Cup]]\n!colspan=2|Continental\n!colspan=2|Total\n|-\n! Division!!Apps!!CS!!Apps!!CS!!Apps!!CS!!Apps!!CS!!Apps!!CS\n|-\n| rowspan=4|[[Reading F.C.|Reading]]\n| [[2003\u201304 Reading F.C. season|2003\u201304]]\n| [[Football League First Division|First Division]]\n| 1||0||0||0||0||0||colspan=2|\u2014\n| 1||0\n|-\n| [[2004\u201305 Reading F.C. season|2004\u201305]]\n| rowspan=2 | [[Football League Championship|Championship]]\n| 0||0||0||0||0||0||colspan=2|\u2014\n| 0||0\n|-\n| [[2005\u201306 Reading F.C. season|2005\u201306]]\n| 0||0||0||0||0||0||colspan=2|\u2014\n| 0||0\n|-\n! colspan=2|Total\n! 1||0||0||0||0||0||colspan=2|\u2014\n! 1||0\n|-\n| [[Rushden & Diamonds F.C.|Rushden & Diamonds]] (loan)\n| [[2005\u201306 Rushden & Diamonds F.C. season|2005\u201306]]\n| rowspa