{"title_page": "Gary Dauberman", "text_new": "{{short description|American screenwriter and director|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Infobox writer\n| image = South by Southwest 2019 8 Gary Dauberman (47338962232) (cropped) (cropped).jpg\n| caption = Dauberman in 2019\n| birth_date = \n| birth_place = \n| years_active = 2007\u2013present\n| nationality = American\n| alma_mater = [[Temple University]]\n| occupation = Screenwriter, director\n| notableworks = [[The Conjuring Universe]]<br/>''[[It (2017 film)|It]]''<br/>''[[It Chapter Two]]''\n}}\n\n'''Gary Dauberman''' is an American screenwriter and director.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.hollywood.com/celebrities/gary-dauberman-57650159/|title=Gary Dauberman {{!}} Biography and Filmography|last=Staff|first=Hollywood.com|date=2015-02-03|work=Hollywood.com|access-date=2017-09-28|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://ihorror.com/interview-screenwriter-gary-dauberman-annabelle-creation/|title=[Interview] Screenwriter Gary Dauberman \u2013 Annabelle: Creation \u2013 Horror Movie News and Reviews|date=2017-07-28|work=Horror Movie News and Reviews|access-date=2017-09-28|language=en-US}}</ref> He is known for writing [[The Conjuring Universe]] horror films ''[[Annabelle (film)|Annabelle]]'' (2014), ''[[Annabelle: Creation]]'' (2017), ''[[The Nun (2018 film)|The Nun]]'' (2018), and ''[[Annabelle Comes Home]]'' (2019). He made his directorial debut with the latter film. Dauberman also co-wrote the supernatural horror film ''[[It (2017 film)|It]]'' (2017), and solely wrote its follow-up ''[[It Chapter Two]]'' (2019), which are based on the [[It (novel)|novel of the same name]].\n\n==Personal life==\nDauberman attended [[Delaware County Community College]] for two years before transferring to [[Temple University]], where he graduated in 2002.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tcm.com/tcmdb/person/11305499%7C0/Gary-Dauberman/biography.html|title=Biography for Gary Dauberman|website=Turner Classic Movies|access-date=2017-09-28}}</ref> He is a Christian.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.gospelherald.com/articles/71234/20170809/christian-annabelle-creation-writer-why-horror-flick-faith-based-film.htm|title=Christian 'Annabelle: Creation' Writer On Why Horror Flick is 'Faith Based Film' (Exclusive Interview)|last=Herald|first=The Gospel|date=2017-08-09|work=Breaking Christian News: World, Business, and More {{!}} The Gospel Herald|access-date=2017-09-28|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-  \n! rowspan=2 style=\"width 33:px;\"|Year\n! rowspan=2|Title\n! colspan=3|Credited as\n! rowspan=2|Notes \n|- \n! width=65 |Director\n! width=\"65\" |Writer\n! width=65 |Producer\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|2007\n|''[[Blood Monkey]]''\n|{{no}}\n|{{Yes}}\n|{{no}}\n|[[Direct-to-video]]; \u0441o-written with [[George LaVoo]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2014\n| ''[[Annabelle (film)|Annabelle]]''\n|{{no}}\n|{{Yes}}\n|{{no}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|2016\n| ''Within''\n|{{no}}\n|{{Yes}}\n|{{no}}\n| \n|-\n| ''[[Wolves at the Door]]''\n|{{no}}\n|{{Yes}}\n|{{no}}\n| \n|-\n| rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\"|2017\n| ''[[Annabelle: Creation]]''\n|{{no}}\n|{{Yes}}\n|{{no}}\n|\n|-\n| ''[[It (2017 film)|It]]''\n|{{no}}\n|{{Yes}}\n|{{no}}\n| Co-screenwriter with Chase Palmer and [[Cary Joji Fukunaga|Cary Fukunaga]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2018\n| ''[[The Nun (2018 film)|The Nun]]''\n|{{no}}\n|{{Yes}}\n|{{Yes|Executive}}\n| Story co-written with [[James Wan]]\n|-\n| rowspan=3 style=\"text-align:center;\"|2019\n| ''[[The Curse of La Llorona]]''\n|{{no}}\n|{{no}}\n|{{Yes}}\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Annabelle Comes Home]]''\n|{{Yes}}\n|{{Yes}}\n|{{no}}\n| [[Directorial debut]]; story co-written with James Wan\n|-\n| ''[[It Chapter Two]]''\n|{{no}}\n|{{Yes}}\n|{{Yes|Executive}}\n| \n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|TBA\n| ''[['Salem's Lot#Film and television|'Salem\u2019s Lot]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Verhoeven|first1=Beatrice|title=Gary Dauberman to Adapt Stephen King\u2019s \u2018Salem\u2019s Lot,\u2019 James Wan to Produce|url=https://www.thewrap.com/gary-dauberman-to-adapt-stephen-kings-salems-lot-james-wan-to-produce/|work=[[The Wrap]]|accessdate=23 April 2019}}</ref>''\n|{{yes}}\n|{{Yes}}\n|{{yes}}\n| \n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-  \n! rowspan=2 style=\"width 33:px;\"|Year\n! rowspan=2|Title\n! colspan=\"2\" |Credited as\n! rowspan=2|Notes \n|-\n! width=65 |Writer\n! width=\"65\" |Executive Producer\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|2007\n|''[[In the Spider's Web]]''\n|{{Yes}}\n|{{no}}\n|Television film\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2008\n| ''[[Swamp Devil]]''\n|{{Yes}}\n|{{no}}\n| Television film; co-written with [[Ethlie Ann Vare]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2019\n| ''[[Swamp Thing (2019 TV series)|Swamp Thing]]''\n|{{Yes}}\n|{{Yes}}\n| Co-written with [[Mark Verheiden]]\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|2477891}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dauberman, Gary}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American male screenwriters]]\n[[Category:Temple University alumni]]\n[[Category:American Christians]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Horror film directors]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American screenwriter and director|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Infobox writer\n| image = South by Southwest 2019 8 Gary Dauberman (47338962232) (cropped) (cropped).jpg\n| caption = Dauberman in 2019\n| birth_date = \n| birth_place = \n| years_active = 2007\u2013present\n| nationality = American\n| alma_mater = [[Temple University]]\n| occupation = Screenwriter, director\n| notableworks = [[The Conjuring Universe]]<br/>''[[It (2017 film)|It]]''<br/>''[[It Chapter Two]]''\n}}\n\n'''Gary Dauberman''' is an American screenwriter and director.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.hollywood.com/celebrities/gary-dauberman-57650159/|title=Gary Dauberman {{!}} Biography and Filmography|last=Staff|first=Hollywood.com|date=2015-02-03|work=Hollywood.com|access-date=2017-09-28|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://ihorror.com/interview-screenwriter-gary-dauberman-annabelle-creation/|title=[Interview] Screenwriter Gary Dauberman \u2013 Annabelle: Creation \u2013 Horror Movie News and Reviews|date=2017-07-28|work=Horror Movie News and Reviews|access-date=2017-09-28|language=en-US}}</ref> He is known for writing [[The Conjuring Universe]] horror films ''[[Annabelle (film)|Annabelle]]'' (2014), ''[[Annabelle: Creation]]'' (2017), ''[[The Nun (2018 film)|The Nun]]'' (2018), and ''[[Annabelle Comes Home]]'' (2019). He made his directorial debut with the latter film. Dauberman also co-wrote the supernatural horror film ''[[It (2017 film)|It]]'' (2017), and solely wrote its follow-up ''[[It Chapter Two]]'' (2019), which are based on the [[It (novel)|novel of the same name]].\n\n==Personal life==\nDauberman attended [[Delaware County Community College]] for two years before transferring to [[Temple University]], where he graduated in 2002.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tcm.com/tcmdb/person/11305499%7C0/Gary-Dauberman/biography.html|title=Biography for Gary Dauberman|website=Turner Classic Movies|access-date=2017-09-28}}</ref> He is a Christian.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.gospelherald.com/articles/71234/20170809/christian-annabelle-creation-writer-why-horror-flick-faith-based-film.htm|title=Christian 'Annabelle: Creation' Writer On Why Horror Flick is 'Faith Based Film' (Exclusive Interview)|last=Herald|first=The Gospel|date=2017-08-09|work=Breaking Christian News: World, Business, and More {{!}} The Gospel Herald|access-date=2017-09-28|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-  \n! rowspan=2 style=\"width 33:px;\"|Year\n! rowspan=2|Title\n! colspan=3|Credited as\n! rowspan=2|Notes \n|- \n! width=65 |Director\n! width=\"65\" |Writer\n! width=65 |Producer\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|2007\n|''[[Blood Monkey]]''\n|{{no}}\n|{{Yes}}\n|{{no